    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pouches serving as talismans used in Angola, Portugal, and Brazil, particularly during 17th-19th centuries. Most information about these objects comes from the records of the Portuguese Inquisition, which accused those who owned or made them of sorcery.</Note_Text>
